
Overview of noun commotion

The noun commotion has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (6) disturbance, disruption, commotion, flutter, hurly burly, to-do, hoo-ha, hoo-hah, kerfuffle -- (a disorderly outburst or tumult; "they were amazed by the furious disturbance they had caused")
2. (2) commotion, din, ruction, ruckus, rumpus, tumult -- (the act of making a noisy disturbance)
3. whirl, commotion -- (confused movement; "he was caught up in a whirl of work"; "a commotion of people fought for the exits")
